WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.491 --> 00:00:01.971
<v ->Imagine lying in your bed,</v>

2
00:00:01.971 --> 00:00:03.811
and suddenly becoming paralyzed,

3
00:00:04.251 --> 00:00:07.945
and transported to a time 5,000 years into the future,

4
00:00:07.945 --> 00:00:09.865
where you're experiencing life through the eyes

5
00:00:09.865 --> 00:00:11.555
and body of a stranger.

6
00:00:12.005 --> 00:00:12.726
Well, this is what happened

7
00:00:12.726 --> 00:00:14.566
to anthropologist Hank Wesselman,

8
00:00:14.566 --> 00:00:17.026
a scientist who spent 25 years

9
00:00:17.026 --> 00:00:18.566
working in the fossil beds,

10
00:00:18.566 --> 00:00:20.786
at the East Africa's Rift Valley,

11
00:00:20.786 --> 00:00:22.476
alongside the Leakey family.

12
00:00:23.006 --> 00:00:24.787
These visionary experiences

13
00:00:24.787 --> 00:00:26.729
put him on an entirely new path,

14
00:00:26.729 --> 00:00:29.089
in his investigations into the evolution

15
00:00:29.089 --> 00:00:31.279
of human beings and our consciousness,

16
00:00:31.279 --> 00:00:32.351
both from the past,

17
00:00:32.351 --> 00:00:33.981
and into the future.

18
00:00:42.511 --> 00:00:44.991
Your background is that as an anthropologist,

19
00:00:44.991 --> 00:00:46.651
and paleontologist.

20
00:00:46.651 --> 00:00:50.497
But not an ordinary story, academically or otherwise,

21
00:00:50.497 --> 00:00:53.339
because you began having some experiences

22
00:00:53.339 --> 00:00:55.519
that were really quite extraordinary,

23
00:00:55.519 --> 00:00:57.939
that started taking you and your work

24
00:00:57.939 --> 00:01:01.449
in an entirely new direction, or a parallel direction.

25
00:01:01.699 --> 00:01:03.939
And this is chronicled in your book "Spiritwalker,"

26
00:01:03.939 --> 00:01:05.539
which I read several years ago.

27
00:01:05.539 --> 00:01:07.740
Fantastic book, very engaging.

28
00:01:08.009 --> 00:01:12.420
What happened that began this path of your work?

29
00:01:12.710 --> 00:01:16.770
<v ->Well, in those days, back in the early 70's,</v>

30
00:01:16.770 --> 00:01:18.370
I got into anthropology,

31
00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:20.762
and for the past 30 years or so,

32
00:01:20.762 --> 00:01:23.262
I've been a member of a team of scientists,

33
00:01:23.512 --> 00:01:25.755
investigating those eroded landscapes

34
00:01:25.755 --> 00:01:28.235
of the Great Rift Valley in Eastern Africa,

35
00:01:28.235 --> 00:01:30.019
looking for the evidence,

36
00:01:30.495 --> 00:01:33.225
for the earliest ancestors of humanity.

37
00:01:33.975 --> 00:01:35.615
We've essentially been looking for the missing link,

38
00:01:35.615 --> 00:01:38.145
that Charles Darwin said we would eventually find.

39
00:01:38.815 --> 00:01:41.535
And so, in the early 70's, I was drawn into this work,

40
00:01:41.535 --> 00:01:43.717
as a graduate student out of UC Berkeley.

41
00:01:44.523 --> 00:01:46.839
And, I found myself rubbing elbows with

42
00:01:46.839 --> 00:01:49.143
individuals like Louis and Mary Leakey,

43
00:01:49.143 --> 00:01:50.639
and their son Richard,

44
00:01:50.639 --> 00:01:53.609
Don Johanson, the man who would later find Lucy.

45
00:01:53.609 --> 00:01:56.305
And I was operating at the highest levels of science.

46
00:01:57.015 --> 00:01:59.802
But it was out there in the deserts of Southwestern Ethiopia

47
00:01:59.802 --> 00:02:02.250
that I began to have what could broadly be called

48
00:02:02.250 --> 00:02:04.252
"visionary experiences".

49
00:02:04.818 --> 00:02:06.882
Now in those days, I had no idea

50
00:02:06.882 --> 00:02:09.316
what visionary experiences were.

51
00:02:09.767 --> 00:02:11.471
You know, I wasn't one of those individuals

52
00:02:11.471 --> 00:02:13.523
who studied for years

53
00:02:13.523 --> 00:02:15.495
at the knees of the wisdom masters,

54
00:02:15.495 --> 00:02:17.236
practicing meditation and yoga,

55
00:02:17.236 --> 00:02:19.602
hoping for transcendent experiences.

56
00:02:19.602 --> 00:02:21.243
You know, this was not my path.

57
00:02:21.243 --> 00:02:23.800
I worshiped solely at the altar of science.

58
00:02:24.237 --> 00:02:28.542
And so, when these early epiphanies occurred for me,

59
00:02:28.542 --> 00:02:30.036
out in the bush in Africa,

60
00:02:30.506 --> 00:02:31.854
I took note of them.

61
00:02:32.254 --> 00:02:34.257
I thought about them a great deal.

62
00:02:34.295 --> 00:02:36.647
And I kind of made cryptic notes in my journals.

63
00:02:36.647 --> 00:02:38.466
This isn't the sort of thing you share with your colleagues

64
00:02:38.466 --> 00:02:41.316
in the field of Paleo-Anthropology, alright?

65
00:02:42.236 --> 00:02:44.353
10 years later, in Berkeley,

66
00:02:44.353 --> 00:02:46.505
I had finished my doctoral dissertation.

67
00:02:46.505 --> 00:02:48.337
I'd gotten my PhD.

68
00:02:48.977 --> 00:02:51.798
I was converting my dissertation into a monograph,

69
00:02:51.798 --> 00:02:53.707
which was published in Switzerland.

70
00:02:54.778 --> 00:02:56.450
And one morning at dawn,

71
00:02:57.001 --> 00:03:00.764
on the heels of a joyous marital encounter...

72
00:03:02.224 --> 00:03:04.055
<v Regina>Okay, I know what you're talking about.</v>

73
00:03:04.055 --> 00:03:04.751
<v ->Okay?</v>

74
00:03:05.001 --> 00:03:06.365
At four o'clock in the morning,

75
00:03:06.365 --> 00:03:10.013
I was precipitated into a visionary state of consciousness,

76
00:03:10.493 --> 00:03:13.512
which was quite frightening initially, because,

77
00:03:13.512 --> 00:03:15.977
suddenly, my physical body was invaded,

78
00:03:15.977 --> 00:03:19.675
by feelings of power or force, or pressure.

79
00:03:19.895 --> 00:03:22.579
It was like I was inside an invisible fist,

80
00:03:22.579 --> 00:03:23.957
which was squeezing.

81
00:03:24.523 --> 00:03:27.665
And I discovered my body was completely paralyzed.

82
00:03:27.933 --> 00:03:30.307
I couldn't even breathe effectively.

83
00:03:30.307 --> 00:03:32.429
I remember gulping for air.

84
00:03:33.019 --> 00:03:36.691
And as my eyelids fluttered, my room disappeared.

85
00:03:37.481 --> 00:03:40.246
I'm lying in bed next to my wife, while this is going on.

86
00:03:40.926 --> 00:03:45.663
And I find myself in this dark forest at night.

87
00:03:45.663 --> 00:03:46.711
Black on black.

88
00:03:46.711 --> 00:03:49.987
I could see trees against the blackness of the night.

89
00:03:49.987 --> 00:03:53.867
And I could smell this very sweet scent,

90
00:03:53.867 --> 00:03:56.579
that suggested flowering trees.

91
00:03:56.739 --> 00:03:58.728
And I'm hear-- you know,

92
00:03:58.728 --> 00:04:01.726
I can feel these enormous feelings of power.

93
00:04:01.726 --> 00:04:04.630
I mean, it's-- you know, the word ecstasy doesn't come close

94
00:04:04.630 --> 00:04:06.680
to what this really felt like.

95
00:04:07.774 --> 00:04:09.594
But my curiosity clicked on.

96
00:04:09.952 --> 00:04:13.414
I discovered my intentions, my thoughts,

97
00:04:13.414 --> 00:04:15.406
were enough to move me here and there.

98
00:04:15.406 --> 00:04:16.732
If I wanted to see something,

99
00:04:17.092 --> 00:04:19.651
I would drift in that direction, and I would see it.

100
00:04:20.221 --> 00:04:21.474
It was in this state,

101
00:04:21.474 --> 00:04:23.226
that I was brought face to face

102
00:04:23.226 --> 00:04:25.540
with what indigenous tribal people would call

103
00:04:26.240 --> 00:04:27.258
a "spirit".

104
00:04:28.244 --> 00:04:30.099
Now, nothing in my training at UC Berkeley

105
00:04:30.099 --> 00:04:31.792
prepared me for this experience.

106
00:04:31.792 --> 00:04:32.700
(Regina chuckles)

107
00:04:32.700 --> 00:04:33.524
Alright?

108
00:04:33.953 --> 00:04:36.435
I was face to face with something truly formidable.

109
00:04:36.435 --> 00:04:38.705
It looked like a gigantic shadow.

110
00:04:39.465 --> 00:04:41.997
I was aware of Jung's concept of the shadow.

111
00:04:41.997 --> 00:04:43.753
This was not a projection of myself,

112
00:04:43.753 --> 00:04:45.051
I knew quite clearly.

113
00:04:45.051 --> 00:04:47.471
This was a large, tall silhouette,

114
00:04:47.741 --> 00:04:49.498
that looked somewhat like a keyhole,

115
00:04:49.498 --> 00:04:51.720
with a little head at the top, shoulders,

116
00:04:51.720 --> 00:04:54.654
and then went all the way down to the ground.

117
00:04:56.230 --> 00:04:57.779
I was face to face with this thing,

118
00:04:57.779 --> 00:05:00.251
and the thought occurred to me that this,

119
00:05:00.251 --> 00:05:01.057
whatever it was,

120
00:05:01.057 --> 00:05:02.663
could be the source of the sensations

121
00:05:02.663 --> 00:05:04.079
that I was experiencing.

122
00:05:04.519 --> 00:05:08.435
With that thought, the (mumbles) was turned up, alright?

123
00:05:08.435 --> 00:05:11.104
And I found myself lifted off the ground,

124
00:05:11.104 --> 00:05:13.106
and gently rotated in space,

125
00:05:13.106 --> 00:05:15.592
with lightning flashing out of my fingertips

126
00:05:15.592 --> 00:05:16.832
and off my shoulders.

127
00:05:18.012 --> 00:05:19.732
It coulda been very frightening,

128
00:05:19.732 --> 00:05:21.290
if I wasn't so curious.

129
00:05:21.290 --> 00:05:23.048
I mean, this is what has been my cross to bear.

130
00:05:23.048 --> 00:05:25.713
This is what got me in to science, my curiosity.

131
00:05:25.713 --> 00:05:26.766
I'm a scholar.

132
00:05:28.486 --> 00:05:31.341
This episode came to an end.

133
00:05:31.981 --> 00:05:34.714
And it peaked my curiosity beyond anything else

134
00:05:34.714 --> 00:05:36.264
I'd experienced in my life.

135
00:05:36.264 --> 00:05:38.385
I mean, when you've had the direct experience of spirit,

136
00:05:38.385 --> 00:05:39.562
everything is different.

137
00:05:40.255 --> 00:05:41.679
I had another one, a week later.

138
00:05:42.229 --> 00:05:44.985
And then a real beauty, about six months later,

139
00:05:44.985 --> 00:05:47.086
just to make sure I was paying attention.

140
00:05:47.242 --> 00:05:50.517
On which, I was taken on a cosmic tour of the universe.

141
00:05:50.717 --> 00:05:53.150
I was taken places and shown things,

142
00:05:53.495 --> 00:05:54.902
which were clearly not here.

143
00:05:54.902 --> 00:05:57.080
They're clearly, if we could use this term,

144
00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:58.826
extraterrestrial.

145
00:05:59.412 --> 00:06:01.788
I was shown extraterrestrial life forms.

146
00:06:01.788 --> 00:06:03.591
Extraterrestrial landscapes.

147
00:06:03.972 --> 00:06:05.494
And at the end of this experience,

148
00:06:05.494 --> 00:06:07.946
I was brought back to my body.

149
00:06:08.232 --> 00:06:09.424
My body wasn't going anywhere.

150
00:06:09.424 --> 00:06:11.416
This was my mind, which was flying.

151
00:06:11.746 --> 00:06:13.253
I was brought back to my body,

152
00:06:13.253 --> 00:06:14.934
in bed, in Berkeley,

153
00:06:14.934 --> 00:06:16.685
on a foggy Berkeley morning.

154
00:06:17.475 --> 00:06:20.008
And, nothing was ever quite the same,

155
00:06:20.008 --> 00:06:21.648
for me, again, after that.

156
00:06:22.502 --> 00:06:24.158
Now, having had these experiences,

157
00:06:24.158 --> 00:06:25.392
I wanted more.

158
00:06:25.766 --> 00:06:27.746
And I wanted it from direct experience.

159
00:06:27.746 --> 00:06:28.934
I didn't wanna read about it.

160
00:06:28.934 --> 00:06:30.384
I wanted to have it.

161
00:06:30.758 --> 00:06:32.592
But I couldn't seem to turn it on again.

162
00:06:33.158 --> 00:06:35.702
Now I took a lot of workshops in Shamanism.

163
00:06:35.702 --> 00:06:37.992
I knew about Shamans, by this time.

164
00:06:37.992 --> 00:06:40.022
As an anthropologist, I would know that.

165
00:06:40.772 --> 00:06:42.130
Now, in the Western world,

166
00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:45.504
when we use the word "shaman," most of us tend to conjure up

167
00:06:45.504 --> 00:06:49.186
an image of a masked and tribal person,

168
00:06:49.186 --> 00:06:51.266
dancing around the fire in the dark,

169
00:06:51.526 --> 00:06:54.115
involved in some mysterious ritual,

170
00:06:54.475 --> 00:06:55.968
accompanied by drum beats.

171
00:06:55.968 --> 00:06:57.658
And that's not a bad description.

172
00:06:58.506 --> 00:07:00.825
But the mask, the costume, the ritual,

173
00:07:00.825 --> 00:07:02.803
these are all cultural things.

174
00:07:03.297 --> 00:07:05.652
And inside that cultural shell,

175
00:07:06.761 --> 00:07:08.738
there's an individual, a man or a woman,

176
00:07:08.738 --> 00:07:10.884
who has a set of very real skills.

177
00:07:11.786 --> 00:07:13.466
Now, all true Shamans

178
00:07:14.246 --> 00:07:16.877
learn or discover that they have this ability

179
00:07:16.877 --> 00:07:19.887
to achieve these expanded awareness states.

180
00:07:20.213 --> 00:07:21.797
We could call then trance states.

181
00:07:21.797 --> 00:07:24.109
But I don't tend to use the word trance, because,

182
00:07:24.109 --> 00:07:26.631
trance implies that you're unconscious.

183
00:07:27.149 --> 00:07:28.902
And this is quite the reverse.

184
00:07:29.225 --> 00:07:32.045
In these states, I was super-conscious.

185
00:07:32.045 --> 00:07:33.321
I was super-conscious.

186
00:07:33.461 --> 00:07:34.997
My consciousness expanded,

187
00:07:34.997 --> 00:07:36.917
beyond my wildest imaginings.

188
00:07:37.483 --> 00:07:39.474
Well, this is what typifies the Shaman.

189
00:07:39.474 --> 00:07:42.505
The Shaman achieves these expanded awareness states.

190
00:07:43.489 --> 00:07:44.629
And it's in these states,

191
00:07:44.629 --> 00:07:46.837
that they disassociate their conscious awareness,

192
00:07:46.837 --> 00:07:48.719
away from their physical body.

193
00:07:49.237 --> 00:07:52.405
And literally enter into, or journey into,

194
00:07:52.405 --> 00:07:53.885
an alternate reality,

195
00:07:53.885 --> 00:07:56.535
which indigenous people call the "Spirit World".

196
00:07:57.029 --> 00:07:58.061
They call it the Spirit World,

197
00:07:58.061 --> 00:07:59.823
because they encounter spirits there.

198
00:08:00.029 --> 00:08:01.253
The spirits of nature,

199
00:08:01.253 --> 00:08:02.285
the spirits of animals,

200
00:08:02.285 --> 00:08:04.016
the spirits of plants,

201
00:08:04.016 --> 00:08:08.165
the spirits of higher divine beings,

202
00:08:08.165 --> 00:08:09.615
the angelic forces,

203
00:08:09.845 --> 00:08:11.957
those compassionate beings who are poised,

204
00:08:11.957 --> 00:08:14.245
just beyond the edges of the reality,

205
00:08:14.245 --> 00:08:16.047
that we all take so much for granted.

206
00:08:16.205 --> 00:08:18.351
Poised to help us in various ways.

207
00:08:18.965 --> 00:08:19.909
In other words, these are

208
00:08:19.909 --> 00:08:22.877
ancient human archetypal experiences,

209
00:08:23.497 --> 00:08:26.849
which the rich diversity of cave and rock art reveals

210
00:08:26.849 --> 00:08:29.907
has been going on for at least 40 to 50,000 years.

211
00:08:31.073 --> 00:08:33.995
Now, I sensed that I was being drawn in this direction,

212
00:08:33.995 --> 00:08:37.261
so I began to take workshops in Shamanism,

213
00:08:37.261 --> 00:08:40.098
and I learned that the Shaman is really a public servant.

214
00:08:41.498 --> 00:08:43.485
The Shaman is able to do various things,

215
00:08:43.485 --> 00:08:44.790
on behalf of others.

216
00:08:45.404 --> 00:08:47.766
Restore power to those who've lost it.

217
00:08:47.973 --> 00:08:50.539
They're able to access information through divination,

218
00:08:50.539 --> 00:08:51.593
from these spirits.

219
00:08:51.919 --> 00:08:53.695
Information of meaning to their client,

220
00:08:53.695 --> 00:08:55.121
who comes to them for help.

221
00:08:55.807 --> 00:08:58.003
They're able to do healing work on various levels,

222
00:08:58.003 --> 00:09:02.301
physical, spiritual, mental, emotional and energetic.

223
00:09:02.991 --> 00:09:04.471
And initially, of course,

224
00:09:04.471 --> 00:09:07.459
as we get drawn into this unusual practice,

225
00:09:08.499 --> 00:09:12.311
we access this experience on behalf of ourselves.

226
00:09:12.311 --> 00:09:14.159
But we find ourselves, ultimately,

227
00:09:14.159 --> 00:09:17.145
drawn in the direction of being of service for others.

228
00:09:17.145 --> 00:09:18.908
And the Spiritwalker story,

229
00:09:18.908 --> 00:09:21.884
is really the story of how I was drawn into this world.

230
00:09:22.764 --> 00:09:24.889
Now, when I lived in Hawaii, right?

231
00:09:24.889 --> 00:09:26.713
This is really the core of that book.

232
00:09:27.763 --> 00:09:30.348
One morning, at four o'clock in the morning,

233
00:09:30.768 --> 00:09:32.211
two, three years later,

234
00:09:33.241 --> 00:09:36.421
the feelings of paralysis appeared in my body once again.

235
00:09:37.563 --> 00:09:39.061
Now, I was waiting for this.

236
00:09:39.723 --> 00:09:41.297
I'd been trying to turn this on again,

237
00:09:42.007 --> 00:09:44.243
for almost three years.

238
00:09:44.243 --> 00:09:45.749
I was waiting for this.

239
00:09:45.952 --> 00:09:49.850
And when it happened, there was a side of me that said,

240
00:09:50.501 --> 00:09:51.458
"Yes!"

241
00:09:51.976 --> 00:09:53.176
You know, that's how I felt.

242
00:09:53.506 --> 00:09:55.823
Now, my conscious awareness, once again,

243
00:09:55.823 --> 00:09:58.009
was drawn out of my physical body,

244
00:09:58.009 --> 00:10:00.158
and I found myself traveling

245
00:10:00.468 --> 00:10:03.547
through this inter-dimensional latticework.

246
00:10:03.957 --> 00:10:08.434
It looked like a matrix, or a grid, or a spider web perhaps.

247
00:10:08.434 --> 00:10:09.263
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

248
00:10:09.263 --> 00:10:10.528
<v ->And it was made of light.</v>

249
00:10:10.528 --> 00:10:13.969
And I seemed to be traveling along a line of light,

250
00:10:13.969 --> 00:10:17.180
towards one of these curious light objects,

251
00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:19.433
that looked very much like the new moon,

252
00:10:19.944 --> 00:10:21.536
in the sense that it was a crescent,

253
00:10:21.536 --> 00:10:22.871
that began to open.

254
00:10:23.248 --> 00:10:24.301
And as the crescent opened,

255
00:10:24.301 --> 00:10:26.005
I began to head right for it, and--

256
00:10:26.005 --> 00:10:27.061
(snaps fingers)

257
00:10:27.471 --> 00:10:29.512
I went through, and I blacked out.

258
00:10:30.050 --> 00:10:31.244
<v Regina>Mmhmm.</v>

259
00:10:31.244 --> 00:10:34.253
<v ->Now, when my conscious awareness clicked on again,</v>

260
00:10:35.753 --> 00:10:37.778
I was in somebody else's body.

261
00:10:38.752 --> 00:10:40.514
<v Regina>Whose, and where, and when?</v>

262
00:10:41.008 --> 00:10:43.005
<v ->Well, this is where it gets really tricky.</v>

263
00:10:43.005 --> 00:10:43.769
<v Regina>Yes.</v>

264
00:10:43.769 --> 00:10:45.415
<v ->I wasn't prepared for this experience.</v>

265
00:10:45.755 --> 00:10:47.948
And my first impulse was shock.

266
00:10:48.778 --> 00:10:51.154
Now, my limited experience with meditation--

