00:14:42.340 --> 00:14:43.828
closed tradition? Or what?

361
00:14:43.828 --> 00:14:46.588
<v ->I was sharing knowledge from the Kahuna tradition--</v>

362
00:14:46.588 --> 00:14:47.278
<v Regina>Yes, right.</v>

363
00:14:47.278 --> 00:14:48.372
<v ->which has never been--</v>

364
00:14:48.372 --> 00:14:49.058
much of which has never been published.

365
00:14:49.058 --> 00:14:50.242
<v Regina>Right, yes.</v>

366
00:14:50.502 --> 00:14:52.698
<v ->And I knew that sooner or later,</v>

367
00:14:53.493 --> 00:14:56.672
the Kahunas were gonna come to look me over,

368
00:14:56.672 --> 00:14:58.026
to see if I was real.

369
00:14:58.760 --> 00:14:59.672
<v Regina>And?</v>

370
00:14:59.672 --> 00:15:02.301
<v ->Well, Spiritwalker came out in 1995,</v>

371
00:15:02.301 --> 00:15:03.501
and it made a huge splash.

372
00:15:03.501 --> 00:15:06.311
In fact, it's been published in 13 languages abroad.

373
00:15:07.261 --> 00:15:11.281
In 1996, I was invited to speak at an institute in Hawaii,

374
00:15:11.281 --> 00:15:12.643
the New Millennium Institute,

375
00:15:12.643 --> 00:15:14.918
which, at that time, was based in a Frank Lloyd Wright house

376
00:15:14.918 --> 00:15:17.530
on the big island of Hawaii, up in Waimea,

377
00:15:17.530 --> 00:15:19.392
where the Parker Ranch is headquartered.

378
00:15:20.030 --> 00:15:21.498
They heard about me,

379
00:15:21.498 --> 00:15:23.376
and they invited me to come and speak.

380
00:15:24.254 --> 00:15:26.028
So I checked it out, you know.

