00:17:00.812 --> 00:17:03.356
Now these guys also had their wives with them.

428
00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:04.388
This was a good sign.

429
00:17:04.388 --> 00:17:06.812
This meant I wasn't gonna be turned into a pillar of salt,

430
00:17:06.812 --> 00:17:08.084
at least not that day.

431
00:17:09.254 --> 00:17:11.219
So, this man was introduced to me.

432
00:17:11.219 --> 00:17:12.767
He has since passed over,

433
00:17:12.767 --> 00:17:14.277
so I can use his name.

434
00:17:14.555 --> 00:17:16.187
His name was Hale Makua.

435
00:17:16.187 --> 00:17:18.921
Hale Kaohalani Makua.

436
00:17:18.921 --> 00:17:23.259
Seven generation direct descendant of King Kamehameha Nui,

437
00:17:23.969 --> 00:17:25.339
on his mother's side.

438
00:17:25.530 --> 00:17:27.267
And seven generation direct descendant

439
00:17:27.267 --> 00:17:29.031
of High Chief Kīwalaʻō,

440
00:17:29.265 --> 00:17:31.007
who was Kamehameha's cousin,

441
00:17:31.007 --> 00:17:32.437
who Kamehameha killed,

442
00:17:32.437 --> 00:17:34.717
to become the Moi, the King.

443
00:17:35.959 --> 00:17:38.053
In other words, this man Makua,

444
00:17:38.053 --> 00:17:40.107
had an exceptional genealogy.

445
00:17:40.121 --> 00:17:40.671
<v Regina>Right.</v>

446
00:17:40.671 --> 00:17:42.973
<v ->I'd been hearing about this guy for years.</v>

447
00:17:43.233 --> 00:17:45.433
This wasn't just any Kahuna who came to hear

448
00:17:45.433 --> 00:17:46.629
what I had to say.

449
00:17:46.886 --> 00:17:48.535
This was the Big Kahuna.

450
00:17:48.535 --> 00:17:49.635
<v Regina>The big Kahuna. (laughs)</v>

451
00:17:49.635 --> 00:17:51.257
<v ->This was the Big Kahuna.</v>

