00:18:47.756 --> 00:18:49.424
"A friend of mine sent me your book.

476
00:18:50.744 --> 00:18:51.740
"And I read it.

477
00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:55.934
<v Regina>That's it.</v>

478
00:18:56.494 --> 00:18:57.082
<v ->Silence--</v>

479
00:18:57.082 --> 00:18:57.510
(Regina laughs)

480
00:18:57.510 --> 00:18:58.508
in the room.

481
00:18:58.508 --> 00:19:01.316
I mean, this was high noon in Polynesia, you know, this wa--

482
00:19:01.316 --> 00:19:02.724
<v Regina>You're waiting for the rest of the story.</v>

483
00:19:02.724 --> 00:19:04.804
<v ->Oh, my God, they're waiting for the other shoe to drop.</v>

484
00:19:05.244 --> 00:19:07.110
He looked at me very seriously, and he said,

485
00:19:07.110 --> 00:19:09.432
"I read it again, just to make sure I got it right.

486
00:19:10.254 --> 00:19:11.752
"And then I went down to the ocean.

487
00:19:11.822 --> 00:19:12.590
"I went down to the beach,

488
00:19:12.590 --> 00:19:14.728
"and I took your book, and I put it down on the sand."

489
00:19:14.750 --> 00:19:15.784
This is in Spiritwalker.

490
00:19:17.454 --> 00:19:18.946
"And I called on the ancestors."

491
00:19:19.766 --> 00:19:21.534
He said, "I called on the ancestors,

492
00:19:21.534 --> 00:19:23.222
"and we had a talk about you."

493
00:19:24.700 --> 00:19:26.164
He looked at me seriously, and he said,

494
00:19:26.164 --> 00:19:28.530
"The ancestors asked me what your name is,

495
00:19:28.530 --> 00:19:30.484
"and I told them your name is Wesselman.

496
00:19:30.484 --> 00:19:31.732
"Hank Wesselman."

497
00:19:32.742 --> 00:19:34.716
And he smiled at this point.

498
00:19:35.259 --> 00:19:38.279
Now, I'm gonna say something from a place of sharing,

499
00:19:38.279 --> 00:19:39.545
not from a place of ego.

500
00:19:39.801 --> 00:19:41.033
He looked at me and he said,

501
00:19:41.033 --> 00:19:42.155
"The ancestors told me

